<p class="courseblockdesc">
Students will examine issues of access and equity through legislation, litigation, and socio-cultural perspectives and be introduced to major theoretical frameworks that influence special education programs. Course Information: Same as <a href="/search/?P=SPED%20461" title="SPED 461" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'SPED 461');">SPED 461</a>. Field work required. Class Schedule Information: To be properly registered, students must enroll in one Lecture-Discussion and one Practice.<br/>
</p>
